abstract: SUB-MARINE, BOAT.--We were present on Friday at the Navy Yard, to witness some experiments made with the newly invented submarine boat. abstract: The U. S. Mail steamer Crescent City, Capt. TANNER, arrived at her wharf last evening from Navy Bay the 21st inst., with $1,500,000 in gold dust, and two hundred and forty passengers, among whom are J. H. MUDD and Judge DAVIS, Delegates to the Whig National Convention; Capt. KANE, U. S. N., and STEPHEN C. MASSETT, Esq., of the Marysville Herald.

abstract: EXECUTION OF JOHN ERPENSTEIN.--The execution of this man, for the murder of his wife, took place at Newark yesterday, in the presence of a large number of persons. He was attended by three clergymen, and met his fate calmly. Previous to his execution he made a written confession of his guilt, which is to be published for the benefit of his children.
